title: Causes random errors with Asterisk
comment: Recently I completed advanced Asterisk training and during the course Linphone was recommended, it worked perfectly during training. Unfortunately when I have tried using Linphone on 2 other Asterisk installations I get an error when a peer using Linphone registers saying "failed to extend from XXX to XXX".   I have spent almost a week now troubleshooting this until yesterday when I tried another client, unfortunately Linphone was causing the error and calls to and from the peers using the Linphone Android client were failing.   After researching and trying a range of fixes for almost a week, all indications point to something wrong with the sip.conf and this may be the case - possibly there is a better codec to use, the codecs installed on the server are ulaw, alaw, gsm and g729a.   I like the app, it's just a pitty that this error keeps coming up on every use of the Linphone Android client with Asterisk.
